   THE STORY OF MARCOS
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Philippine officials were asked repeatedly whether the Aquino government's refusal to allow Marcos to return to the country would remain in effect after his death. Marcos has his rights, I still have to consider the rights and the interests of millions of Filipinos," Aquino told reporters at the presidential palace . His frail body attached to a respirator and a hemodialysis blood-cleansing machine, Marcos is unconscious most of the time but occasionally shows faint signs of life, doctors in Hawaii said . Radio stations here broadcast hourly reports on Marcos' condition .
